ughttolife/people/ignazsemmelweis.aspx?keywords=microbiologist|publisher=Science Museum, London-Brought To Life, Exploring the History of Medicine |location=London, UK| accessdate=2015-09-07}}</ref> |- | <!--year-->1853 - 1938 | <!--image-->[[File:Hans Christian Gram.png|75px]] | <!--name-->[[Hans Christian Gram]] | <!--nationality-->Danish | <!--Contribution summary--> Developed the [[Gram stain]] used to identify and classify bacteria.<ref name= Pommerville2013/><!-- page 21 --> |- | <!--year-->1845 - 1922 | <!--image-->[[File:Charles Laveran nobel.jpg|75px]] | [[Charles Louis Alphonse Laveran|<!--name-->Charles Lavaran]] | <!--nationality-->French | <!--Contribution summary-->1907 Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine for discovering the causative agents of [[malaria]] and [[trypanosomiasis]].<ref name= Pommerville2013/><!-- page 21 --> |- | <!--year-->1827 - 1912 | <!--image-->[[File:Joseph Lister 1902.jpg|75px]] | <!--name-->[[Joseph Lister, 1st Baron Lister|Joseph Lister]] | <!--nationality-->English | <!--Contribution summary-->Introduced sterilisation techniques to surgery.<ref name= Pommerville2013/><!-- page 17 --><ref>{{cite web | title=Joseph Lister (1827-1912) |publisher=Science Museum, London-Brought To Life, Exploring the History of Medicine| url=http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/broughttolife/people/josephlister.aspx |location=London| accessdate=2015-09-07 }}</ref> |- | <!--year-->1822 - 1895 | <!--image-->[[File:Louis Pasteur, foto av Paul Nadar, Crisco edit.jpg|75px]] | <!--name-->[[Louis Pasteur]] | <!--nationality-->French | <!--Contribution summary-->Seminal discoveries in vaccination, [[pasteurization|food safety]], and microbial fermentatoion. A key proponent of the [[germ theory of disease]].<ref name= Pommerville2013/><!-- pages16-17 --> |- | <!--year-->1850 - 1934 | <!--image-->[[File:Fannie Hess.JPG|75px]] | <!--name-->[[Fanny Hesse]] | <!--nationality-->German | <!--Contribution summary-->Developed [[agar]] for use in culturing bacteria.<re